<br>
They have quite a bit more utility than potions and Tboots because of the insta cast.  They run out mid-kite and it's no big deal.  And later on they're great for raids when you need instant cast buffs to get &quot;junk&quot; buffs back up quickly for dispelling mobs.<br>
<br>
Money wise, an MQ is worth about 500 SoW potions (5k for the MQ, 10pp per potion).  At 2.5 per hour or so, that's 200 hours, or 9 days of play time.  Think you'll be 51 with 3 AA's in 9 days of play time?  If so, maybe SoW potions is the way to go.<br>
<br>
So yeah, if you can afford it (either the money, or the further time invested), get them.  You're probably going to have more luck buying the MQ.  Even should you ever see the AC, at level 30 some higher level is going to get the kill if they are around and choose to do so. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=61820 ">Worthing Wrathcaster</a><br> Sorcerer<br>
