<br>
1.) Get a higher level wizzy to come with you - 49+ - Must have SuperNova or better (in terms of mana efficiency).<br>
<br>
2.) Pull every mob in the desert. Don't loose the egro due to running out in front. It may be best to get a higher level melee as at your level, even a little bit of damage from all those mobs will hurt/kill you.<br>
<br>
3.) Have your friend kill them all with a PB AE.<br>
<br>
4.) Rinse/Repeat.<br>
<br>
A while ago, Verant change the number of green mobs that will attack you. It used to be that only 4 mobs would attack you at a given time. Now ALL mobs that egro you will attack you, regardless of level. <br>
<br>
We were pulling 30+ mobs on every pull. Spawned 4SG's, 1 Terratarantua, and 1 AC. <br>
<br>
This technique works great also on farming other areas as well. Now lets hope they don't nerf this as well.<br>
